4 Section 2. Section 5-2-302, MCA, is amended to read:
5 "5-2-302. Compensation and expenses when legislature not in session. When the legislature is
6 not in session, a member of the legislature, while engaged in legislative business authorized interim, interim
7 budget, or administrative committee legislative business or as otherwise provided by law, and with prior
8 authorization of the appropriate funding authority, is entitled to: compensation and expenses as set forth in this
9 section.
10 (1) A legislator participating remotely is entitled to a salary equal to one full day's pay at the rate
11 described in 5-2-301(1) for each 24-hour period.
12 (2) A legislator attending a meeting in person is entitled to the following compensation and
13 expenses based on the number of round-trip miles from the legislator's residence to the meeting:
14 (a) for 100 miles or less:
15 (i) a salary equal to one full day's pay at the rate described in 5-2-301(1) for each 24-hour period;
16 (ii) a mileage allowance as provided in 2-18-503; and
17 (iii) a meal allowance for one midday meal as provided in 2-18-501;
18 (b) for more than 100 miles and less than 400 miles:
19 (i) a salary equal to two full days' pay at the rate described in 5-2-301(1);
20 (ii) a mileage allowance as provided in 2-18-503;
21 (iii) a meal allowance for two morning meals, two midday meals, and two evening meals as
22 provided in 2-18-501; and
23 (iv) two nights' lodging reimbursed at the prescribed maximum standard federal rate for each day
24 for the location; or
25 (c) for 400 miles or more:
26 (i) a salary equal to three full days' pay at the rate described in 5-2-301(1);
27 (ii) a mileage allowance as provided in 2-18-503;
28 (iii) a meal allowance for three morning meals, three midday meals, and three evening meals as
